createBid(uint256).details: This contract only accepts payment in ETH.

getPrices(uint256).details: Returns prices in reverse order, meaning prices[0] will be the most recent auction price. Skips auctions where there was no winner, i.e. no bids. Reverts if getting a empty data for an auction that happened, e.g. historic data not filled Reverts if there's not enough auction data, i.e. reached token id 0

params.auctionCount: The number of price observations to get.

getSettlements(uint256).details: Returns up to `auctionCount` settlements in reverse order, meaning settlements[0] will be the most recent auction price. Includes auctions with no bids (blockTimestamp will be > 1)

params.auctionCount: The number of price observations to get.

returns.settlements: An array of type `Settlement`, where each Settlement includes a timestamp, the tokenId of that auction, the winning bid amount, and the winner's address.

getSettlements(uint256,uint256).details: Returns prices in chronological order, as opposed to `getSettlements(count)` which returns prices in reverse order. Includes auctions with no bids (blockTimestamp will be > 1)

params.endId: end tokenId (up to, but not including).
params.startId: the first tokenId to get prices for.

returns.settlements: An array of type `Settlement`, where each Settlement includes a timestamp, the tokenId of that auction, the winning bid amount, and the winner's address.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pause().details: This function can only be called by the owner when the contract is unpaused. While no new auctions can be started when paused, anyone can settle an ongoing auction.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

settleAuction().details: This function can only be called when the contract is paused.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause(string).details: This function can only be called by the owner when the contract is paused. If required, this function will start a new auction.

MAX_TIME_BUFFER().notice: A hard-coded cap on time buffer to prevent accidental auction disabling if set with a very high value.

auctionDuration().notice: The auctionDuration of a single auction

base().notice: The Registrar Controller that the auction uses to mint the names

createBid(uint256).notice: Create a bid for a token, with a given amount.

getSettlements(uint256,uint256).notice: Get a range of past auction settlements.

getSettlementsFromIdtoTimestamp(uint256,.notice: Get all past auction settlements starting at `startId` and settled before or at `endTimestamp`.

maxAuctionCount().notice: the maximum number of auctions count to prevent excessive gas usage.

minBidIncrementPercentage().notice: The minimum percentage difference between the last bid amount and the current bid

paymentReceiver().notice: The address that will receive funds after closing the auction

reservePrice().notice: The minimum price accepted in an auction

resolver().notice: The resolver that the auction uses to resolve the names

setMinBidIncrementPercentage(uint8).notice: Set the auction minimum bid increment percentage.

setPaymentReceiver(address).notice: Allows the `owner` to set the reverse registrar contract.

settleCurrentAndCreateNewAuction(string).notice: Settle the current auction, mint a new name, and put it up for auction.

timeBuffer().notice: The minimum amount of time left in an auction after a new bid is created

weth().notice: The address of the WETH contract
